&lt;p&gt;Date: &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 10-27-2025&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;RE:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Arrest Made on Threat to Lincoln City Cultural Center&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Lincoln City Police Department announces the arrest of a suspect in the September 13&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; mass-shooting threat at the Lincoln City Cultural Center.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On October 27, 2025 LCPD detectives, in collaboration with the Keizer Police Department, arrested a 15-year-old juvenile male resident of Keizer.&amp;nbsp; This male was charged with Disorderly Conduct in the First Degree and lodged at the Marion County Juvenile Department.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Due to his age, LCPD is unable to release the suspect&rsquo;s name.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is still an on-going investigation and more details may be released in the future.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Lincoln City Police Department would like to thank the Keizer Police Department, the Marion County District Attorney&rsquo;s Office, and the Marion County Juvenile Department for their assistance in this case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

