&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sherman County, Ore. (Nov. 5, 2025)-&lt;/strong&gt; On Tuesday, November 4, 2025, at 5:35 p.m., Oregon State Police responded to a two-vehicle crash on Highway 97, near milepost 43, in Sherman County.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The preliminary investigation indicated a northbound Chevrolet Impala, operated by Eric Neal Barton (66) of Corvallis, crossed into the southbound lane and struck a southbound International Harvester commercial motor vehicle and trailer, operated by Preston Dejion Shepherd (35) of Hanford (CA), near the rear drive tires.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The operator of the Chevrolet (Barton) was declared deceased at the scene.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The operator of the International Harvester (Shepherd) was reportedly uninjured.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The highway was impacted for approximately four hours during the on-scene investigation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OSP was assisted by the Sherman County Sheriff's Office and ODOT.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

