&lt;div class="_1mf _1mj" style="position: relative; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:inherit"&gt;Division Chief Mark Fitzwater&rsquo;s career began at an early age, inspired by his father, who served as the District&rsquo;s training officer. He first participated in a burn-to-learn exercise at age sixteen &mdash; a moment that confirmed his passion for the fire service. After graduating from Lebanon High School in 2002, he joined the District as a volunteer firefighter and became a full-time firefighter/paramedic in 2007.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family: &amp;quot;Optimistic 95&amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; color: rgb(28, 43, 51); font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;
&lt;div class="_1mf _1mj" style="position: relative; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
