&lt;div class="_1mf _1mj" style="position: relative; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:inherit"&gt;Over the years, Fitzwater has served as Engineer/Medic, Lieutenant, Battalion Chief, and Division Chief of Training, earning a reputation for professionalism and mentorship.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family: &amp;quot;Optimistic 95&amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; color: rgb(28, 43, 51); font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;
&lt;div class="_1mf _1mj" style="position: relative; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family: &amp;quot;Optimistic 95&amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; color: rgb(28, 43, 51); font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;
&lt;div class="_1mf _1mj" style="position: relative; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:inherit"&gt;&ldquo;I always wanted to work at LFD because this is my hometown,&rdquo; Fitzwater said. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s difficult to move away from training because I truly enjoy it, but our District is experiencing growing pains with increased call volume and limited staffing. I feel I can best support our personnel and community by moving into operations.&rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style="font-family: &amp;quot;Optimistic 95&amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; color: rgb(28, 43, 51); font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;
&lt;div class="_1mf _1mj" style="position: relative; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
