&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;42&lt;sup&gt;nd&lt;/sup&gt; Annual Douglas County Christmas Tree Lighting Ceremony&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sunday, November 30, 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Douglas County, Ore.) Douglas County Commissioners Tim Freeman, Tom Kress, and Chris Boice are excited to officially kick off the Christmas Season with the lighting of the &lt;a name="_Hlk150424993"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;42&lt;sup&gt;nd&lt;/sup&gt; Annual &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Douglas County Christmas Tree&lt;/strong&gt; on Sunday, November 30, 2025, at 6:00 pm on the front lawn of the Douglas County Courthouse.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That night we will flip the switch and light up the Douglas County Heritage Christmas Tree and the Douglas County Courthouse for the first time this holiday season. The family-friendly event is free and open to kids of all ages.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;The lights on the Douglas County Christmas Tree and Courthouse will be on display throughout the holiday season. Click on the link below for a sneak peek at the theme for the &lt;strong&gt;42&lt;sup&gt;nd&lt;/sup&gt; Annual Douglas County Christmas Tree Lighting &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/DouglasCountyeGovernment/videos/528782276685674"&gt;https://www.facebook.com/DouglasCountyeGovernment/videos/528782276685674 &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;2025 Douglas County Christmas Tree Lighting Ceremony&lt;/strong&gt; represents a longstanding collaboration between the &amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://douglascounty-oregon.us/"&gt;Douglas County Board of Commissioners&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.cityofroseburg.org/"&gt;City of Roseburg&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.roseburgfcc.org/"&gt;Roseburg&rsquo;s First Christian Church&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;. &amp;nbsp;The evening&rsquo;s festivities include a family-oriented program with music presented by the &lt;strong&gt;Hucrest Community Choir&lt;/strong&gt;, under the direction of Colin Hurowitz; the reading of a traditional Christmas story; tree lighting; and a visit from the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Jolly Old Elf himself&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, Santa Claus.&amp;nbsp; Across the street from the courthouse Roseburg&rsquo;s First Christian Church and Journey Church will once again present a live nativity scene. The hospitality tent sponsored by the Douglas County Board of Commissioners and First Christian Church will feature hot cocoa, coffee and cookies served by the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://missdouglascounty.org/"&gt;Miss Douglas County Scholarship Program&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp; Special thanks to the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.douglascountyor.gov/539/Board-of-Commissioners"&gt;Douglas County Commissioners&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.cityofroseburg.org/"&gt;City of Roseburg&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.roseburgfcc.org/"&gt;Roseburg&rsquo;s First Christian Church&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.cityofroseburg.org/departments/police"&gt;Roseburg Police Department&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.cityofroseburg.org/departments/fire"&gt;Roseburg Fire Department&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.dcso.com/"&gt;Douglas County Sheriff&rsquo;s Office&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://douglascountyor.gov/357/Public-Works"&gt;Douglas County Public Works Department&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://douglascountyor.gov/211/Facilities-Department"&gt;Douglas County Facilities Department&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.douglascountyor.gov/783/Public-Affairs-Office"&gt;Douglas County Public Affairs Department&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://hucrest.roseburg.k12.or.us/"&gt;Hucrest Elementary School&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://missdouglascounty.org/"&gt;Miss Douglas County Scholarship Program&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;/strong&gt;and of course &lt;strong&gt;Santa Claus&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For those not able to attend in-person, the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;2025 Douglas County Tree Lighting Ceremony&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; will be live-streamed on the Douglas County Government Facebook page starting at 6:00 pm on Sunday, November 30, 2025.&amp;nbsp; To watch visit&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/DouglasCountyeGovernment"&gt;https://www.facebook.com/DouglasCountyeGovernment&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp; The public is also invited to take a stroll through Downtown Roseburg this holiday season! Enjoy the festive storefronts and sparkling Christmas lights while supporting our local businesses, shops, and restaurants.&amp;nbsp; A special thank you to Downtown Roseburg&rsquo;s Christmas Light display organizer Zachary Weiss and his league of volunteers for helping bring Christmas cheer to downtown Roseburg.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The Commissioners and staff here at Douglas County government would like to take the opportunity to wish you and your family a wonderful Thanksgiving, a very Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year!&amp;nbsp; For more information about the 42&lt;sup&gt;nd&lt;/sup&gt; Annual Douglas County Christmas Tree Lighting Ceremony visit &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.douglascountyor.gov/"&gt;www.douglascountyor.gov&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; or contact the Douglas County Public Affairs Office at (541) 957-4896 or by email at &lt;a href="mailto:dcinfo@douglascountyor.gov"&gt;dcinfo@douglascountyor.gov&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

