&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:calibri,calibri_embeddedfont,calibri_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt;&ldquo;Increasing housing supply is the single most important way to make life better and more affordable for Oregonians,&rdquo; said OHCS Executive Director Andrea Bell.&amp;nbsp;&ldquo;We want Oregon to be a place where everyone can thrive. A place where people's fundamental needs are met, businesses can grow, and communities are strengthened by locally driven solutions. We cannot afford to wait or be incremental in our actions to bring about this future.&rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:calibri,calibri_embeddedfont,calibri_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

